Credit Risk Manager
Credit Risk Manager
Location:  Singapore
Credit Risk Manager – Permanent – Singapore
Amoria Bond is pleased to offer an excellent opportunity with a global MNC in Singapore. The successful candidate will be in charge of managing all aspects of my client’s credit & risk management activities.
Responsibilities include the following:
•	Preparation of market analyses, asset and credit portfolio for the board and management team
•	Consistently monitoring on account receivables and following up on overdue collections
•	Conducting
risk reviews and due diligence with regards to the credit quality of counterparties involving current/potential customers and key suppliers
•	Responsible for maintaining and building comprehensive database of financial information, portfolio analysis and credit risk assessment.
•	Any other adhoc tasks that are being assigned
Requirements:
•	Excellent academic background, preferably in Finance or Accountancy
•	Ideally candidates with risk management and credit analysis experience with proven records within the banking industry
•	Possess excellent communication and interpersonal skills is essential for this role
•	Must be willing to travel on a short notice
•	Possess strong knowledge of financial statement and must be familiar with international accounting standards
•	Must be able to work with minimum supervision and possess excellent decision making and analytical skills.
Salaries will be competitive and the successful candidate will be compensated based on relevant experience and skill set.
For interested candidates, please kindly forward a copy of your up to date CV in word format to eileen.limcv@amoriabond.com for full details and immediate interview.
Amoria Bond operates as an employment agency and employment business. No terminology in this advert is intended to discriminate on the grounds of age, and we confirm that we are happy to accept applications from persons of any age for this role.
